<figure class="banner tac man mtxl pan">
    <img src="assets/images/welcome-banner.jpg">
</figure>


<div class="row mtxl">

    <section class="large-6 columns taj">

        <h4 class="mtl">Overwhelmed?</h4>

        <p>
            Valoritization is a simple tool to step back and to know where to start.
            It works for every situation when you have to much on your plate. If you want an
            efficient way to deal with them, you just found it!
        </p>

        <ul>
            <li>You have an exam tomorrow and you are 10 chapters behind?</li>
            <li>You need an easy way of getting everyone to agree on a plan?</li>
            <li>You want to realize a personal project? I
              {{#if model}}
                {{#link-to 'matrix' model}}used{{/link-to}}
              {{else}}
                  used
              {{/if}} Valoritization while creating it.
            </li>
        </ul>

    </section>

    <section class="large-6 columns tac">

        <h5>Setup your matrix:</h5>

        <div class="panel">
            <ol class="small-block-grid-3 " type="1">
              {{notice-step icon="fa-cart-plus" number="1" text="Choose your value metric"}}
              {{notice-step icon="fa-industry" number="2" text="Choose your cost metric"}}
              {{notice-step icon="fa-list-ul" number="3" text="List your tasks"}}
            </ol>
        </div>

        <h5>Optimize your work:</h5>

        <div class="panel ">
            <ol class="small-block-grid-3" type="1">
              {{notice-step icon="fa-ban" number="1" text="Identify the traps"}}
              {{notice-step icon="fa-bolt" number="2" text="Do the quick-wins"}}
              {{notice-step icon="fa-cut" number="3" text="Cut the bigger tasks"}}
            </ol>
        </div>

    </section>
</div>

<section class="row taj ptxl">
    <div class="large-12 columns">
        <div class="panel mbn pbn">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="large-8 columns">
                    <p>
                    <h4>You want to give it a try?</h4>
                    No sign-up, just click!
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="large-4 columns tac">
                  {{#link-to 'matrices.new' class='radius button right expand'}}
                      Create a new Matrix
                  {{/link-to}}
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>